:: INTRO-100 Briefing [daytime history-root]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
/* Scene state object — persists across passages (unlike $temp which resets) */
<<set $briefing to {}>>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
The diner smells like coffee that's been on the burner since six and bacon grease that's been in the ventilation since before the <<term "Diefenbunker">> was built.  A place on <<term "Bank Street">> south of Gloucester, no sign worth reading, where the booths are brown vinyl and the light is the colour of weak tea.  Half the clientele are civil servants eating before the buildings open, career government workers worried that the minority Liberal parliament might lose a confidence vote.  Nobody looks at you twice, which is the point.

You're early.  You're always early for Robert.  Mostly because it pisses him off.  He loves you for it though.

[[Sip your coffee.|INTRO-101 Lost in thought]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-105 Waiting [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
The waitress brings coffee without being asked — you've been here before, enough times that she recognizes the booth but not your name.  Her name is Gladys.  You wrap your hands around the mug and watch the door.

Outside, an <<term "OC Transpo">> bus grinds past on <<term "Bank Street" "Bank">>, throwing diesel haze across the sidewalk.  September in Ottawa.  Still warm, but the light has changed — that particular quality of autumn sun that makes the limestone go yellow.

<<if $player.background eq "RCMP constable">>You used to drink coffee like this at the detachment — institutional, slightly burnt.  The ritual is the same even if the context has shifted.
<<elseif $player.background eq "CSIS analyst">>You used to meet sources in places like this.  The tradecraft is the same.
<<elseif $player.background eq "grad student">>There's a woman two booths over eating eggs alone and staring at nothing.  The part of your brain that studied behavioural patterns can't stop reading the room.  You look away.  Not a case study.
<<else>>Two years ago you wouldn't have known what to look for in a diner — the exits, the sightlines, the two men at the counter reading the same section of the Citizen.
<</if>>

[[Continue|INTRO-110 Robert arrives]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-110 Robert arrives [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
<img src="media/characters/robert-flett-diner-entry.png" alt="Robert Flett entering the diner" class="passage-header-image">

Robert Flett arrives at 8:14, which means he was in the neighbourhood by 7:45 and spent the intervening time making sure he wasn't followed.  You know this because he taught you to do the same thing, and because he's carrying a copy of the <<term "Globe">> that looks like it's already been read.  It's a ridiculous thing to do half a block from the office, but it's //because// you're a known regular here — Robert dropping in once doesn't read as a meet.  You smile that he does the newspaper bit anyway.

He doesn't look like a man who tracks the inexplicable for a living.  He looks like a mid-level bureaucrat — brown skin you've long since placed as <<term "Métis">>, hair going grey at the temples, a jacket that's seen better years.  He grew up in <<term "Shield country">> between the <<term "Sault">> and <<term "Thunder Bay">>.

[[The one thing that doesn't match is his hands.|INTRO-115 Morning]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-115 Morning [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Working hands, scarred across the knuckles.  You noticed them the first day you met him, two years ago, and you still don't know the story.  Especially since you do know the story of how he was an academic at <<term "Lakehead">> and a star grad student at <<term "U of T">>.  But who knows what he's seen in the dark of the woods.

He slides into the booth across from you, sets the <<term "Globe">> on the table, and catches the waitress's eye.  Coffee.  No food yet.

"Morning," he says.

[["Morning."|INTRO-200 Assignment]]
[["You look tired."|INTRO-200a Personal]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-200a Personal [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He gives you a look and a smile.  "Well fuck you too, junior."  He takes the coffee from the waitress, adds one cream, stirs it exactly three times.  Same as always.

No folder this time, no laptop.  Robert looks at you for a moment with that particular expression he gets when he's about to tell you something he's been thinking about for a while.

"I have an assignment for you," he says.  "Your first sustained field placement."

[[The weight of those words settles over the table.|INTRO-205 Field placement]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-200 Assignment [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He nods.  Takes the coffee from the waitress, adds one cream, stirs it exactly three times.  Same as always.

No folder this time, no laptop.  Robert looks at you for a moment with that particular expression he gets when he's about to tell you something he's been thinking about for a while.

"I have an assignment for you," he says.  "Your first sustained field placement."

[[The weight of those words settles over the table.|INTRO-205 Field placement]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-205 Field placement [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He pauses.  Two years of training, two years of reading case files and attending seminars on <<term "NYSE">> classification protocols and learning to shoot at a range in Carp that the <<term "Branch">> pretends is a conservation club.

This is what it was for.

"There's a club on Queen West," he says.

Huh, Toronto.  That's odd.  Most NYSE incidents are further north.  Also, a Toronto field placement is a plum assignment — someone more senior would surely be fighting for it.  There must be a catch.

"Members-only.  Been operating for about two years.  Called Sizzle."

He says the name without inflection, like it's a case number.

"It's a swingers club."

Ah, there it is.

[[You raise an eyebrow.|INTRO-210 Swingers club]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-210 Swingers club [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Another pause.  Robert is very good at pauses.  But so are you.

"The <<term "Branch">> has been tracking anomalous reports associated with the club and its membership for the past fourteen months.  Behavioural changes in regular members — progressive, directional, consistent enough to flag <<term "NYSE">> classification."

He takes a sip of coffee.  Puts the mug down.

"We don't have anyone inside.  We need someone inside."

No shit, Bob.

[["What kind of anomalous?"|INTRO-300 NYSE details]]
[["What's my cover?"|INTRO-310 Cover]]
[["A swingers club."|INTRO-320 Reaction]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-300 NYSE details [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert turns his coffee mug a quarter rotation.  He does this when he's choosing his words.

"Influence patterns," he says.  "Members who've been attending regularly show progressive changes in behaviour and personality.  Not sudden — gradual.  Each step looks like a natural extension of the one before it.  A person who was relatively conservative six months ago is now doing things they wouldn't have imagined a year prior."

Another pause.  "Ass fisting," he says dryly.

You raise an eyebrow.  He almost grins.  He's giving you shit.

"The escalation is the signature."

[[Continue|INTRO-305 NYSE continued]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-305 NYSE continued [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"We've also picked up reports of intrusive ideation.  Desires that feel implanted rather than organic.  Attraction to specific individuals that doesn't match established patterns.  Some reports of altered time perception inside the club.  Memory inconsistencies."

<<if $player.background eq "CSIS analyst">>You recognize the briefing structure — he's presenting the indicators without the conclusion, letting you draw it yourself.  An analyst's habit.
<</if>>

"Everything we have is secondhand.  A therapist.  A spouse.  An acquaintance we recruited.  The members themselves don't know they're being observed."

He meets your eyes.  "Which is why we need primary observation."

[["What's actually causing it?"|INTRO-330 Source]]
[["Walk me through the operational setup."|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-310 Cover [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He almost smiles.  Almost.

"Straight to operational.  Good."  He shifts in the booth, leaning forward slightly — the shift from briefing officer to handler.

"The cover is employment.  You're going to get a job at Sizzle.  Not as a member — as staff.  Bartender, hostess, coat check — whatever they're hiring for.  The Branch will set you up with an apartment in the neighbourhood, a backstory, documents."

"Nothing suspicious about a young woman wanting a job at a bar."

[[Continue|INTRO-315 Cover continued]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-315 Cover continued [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"The objective is access.  Get inside, observe, report.  Build relationships with staff and regular members.  Watch for anything that matches the <<term "NYSE">> indicators."

He leans back.

"The secondary objective — the reason we're not sending someone from Metro Police — is that you have <<term "NYSE">> training.  You know what to look for and, more importantly, you know what it feels like when something isn't right."

[["What kind of anomalous reports are we talking about?"|INTRO-300 NYSE details]]
[["Why me specifically?"|INTRO-340 Why me]]
[["What are the risks?"|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-320 Reaction [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
You say it flat.  The words sit between you on the table.

Robert doesn't blink.  "A swingers club.  Members-only, well-established, well-regarded within its community.  Not a front.  A functioning club with a real membership, real events, real —" he pauses — "activities.  That is the operational environment."

There's a silence.  The waitress passes with a pot of coffee.  Somewhere in the kitchen, someone drops a plate and swears in Greek.

[["Walk me through it."|INTRO-325 No concerns]]
[["I'm not doing it."|INTRO-322 Concerns]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-325 No concerns [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"The assignment is intelligence-gathering in a sexually explicit environment," Robert says.  "That is what it is.  The <<term "NYSE">> element is why it's Branch instead of Vice.  If you have concerns about the nature of the work, this is the time to raise them."

<<if $player.background eq "grad student">>You wrote a thesis chapter on environments like this — the social dynamics, the consent frameworks, the group psychology.
<<elseif $player.background eq "unemployed after university">>You've been in places like this.  Not as an agent — as a person.  That's a different kind of knowledge.
<</if>>

[["No concerns.  Walk me through it."|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
[["What kind of anomalous reports are we talking about?"|INTRO-300 NYSE details]]
[["Why me specifically?"|INTRO-340 Why me]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-330 Source [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert is quiet for a moment.  It's a different quiet than his briefing pauses.

"We don't know," he says.  And then, because he's Robert: "The <<term "Branch">> has classified the source as undetermined.  Current working hypotheses include an individual or individuals with anomalous capabilities, an environmental factor, or a combination."

He picks up his coffee, looks at it, puts it back down.

"In my experience —" he starts, then catches himself.  Starts again with the government version.  "In cases with this profile, there's usually a focal point."

[[Continue|INTRO-335 Focal point]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-335 Focal point [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"Something or someone that's generating the effect.  Finding that focal point is part of what you'll be looking for."

<<skillCheck "Academic" "2d6" $player.skills.academic.level 8>>
<<success>>
You catch the shift.  //In my experience.//  Robert has seen cases like this before.  He was going to say something from that experience, and then he put the government language back on.

You file that away.

"But that's secondary to primary observation," he says, back on firm procedural ground.  "Your first priority is establishing cover and reporting what you see.  Don't go looking for the source.  Let the picture come to you."

[["Understood.  Walk me through the operational setup."|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
<<failure>>
Whatever Robert almost said disappears back into the briefing.  You can feel the gap in the answer, but not what was behind it.

"But that's secondary to primary observation," he says, back on firm procedural ground.  "Your first priority is establishing cover and reporting what you see.  Don't go looking for the source.  Let the picture come to you."

[["Understood.  Walk me through the operational setup."|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
<</skillCheck>>
<</page>>


:: INTRO-340 Why me [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert's expression doesn't change, but something behind it shifts — a microsecond of professional discomfort.

"The assignment requires a credibly attractive woman under thirty who has completed <<term "Branch">> <<term "NYSE">> training and can sustain a cover identity in a high-pressure social environment."  He says this like he's reading it from a personnel form.  "The talent pool matching those criteria is small."

He takes three deliberate sips of coffee to put space between the clinical assessment and whatever comes next.

You've known Robert a while now.  This is maybe the first time you can remember when he isn't meeting your eyes.

[[Continue|INTRO-345 Qualified]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-345 Qualified [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"You're good at reading people.  You can hold a conversation and a cover simultaneously.  You don't rattle easily.  And you understand <<term "NYSE">> classification well enough to recognize indicators in the field."

<<if $player.background eq "grad student">>You studied persuasion and influence for two years.  You know when someone is framing a limited choice as a compliment.  Right now, Robert is not saying: //and I don't have anyone else.//
<<elseif $player.background eq "RCMP constable">>Three years of reading people on traffic stops and domestic calls taught you when someone is leaving something out.  Robert means everything he just said.  He also means something he didn't say.
<<else>>You read the obvious answer around his list of qualifications.  The Branch doesn't have many options, and you're the best one.
<</if>>

"I wouldn't send you if I didn't think you could do it," he adds.  Quieter.  Not government anymore — Robert.

[["Walk me through the operational details."|INTRO-400 Apartment]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-400 Apartment [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert reaches into his jacket and pulls out a single sheet of paper, folded twice.  He unfolds it on the table between the coffee mugs.  An address, a phone number, a short list in his careful handwriting.

"Operational details," he says, and now he's all handler.

"The Branch is setting up an apartment for you in Parkdale — close enough to the club to be plausible, far enough to not be conspicuous.  You'll have it by Wednesday.  Furnished, first and last covered through a shell company.  Cover name and documents will be ready by then."

[[Continue|INTRO-405 Reporting]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-405 Reporting [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He taps the paper.

"You'll report to me directly.  Once a week to start, in-person, locations rotate.  If you need me urgently, there's a contact protocol — I'll walk you through it at the office."

He holds your gaze.

"If your cover is compromised — if someone at the club identifies you as Branch or law enforcement — you walk out.  Immediately.  You do not try to recover the cover.  You leave, you go to a pre-arranged location, and you wait for extraction."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-410 Rules [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"One more thing.  Don't go looking for the <<term "NYSE">> directly.  Don't break cover to investigate.  Be patient.  You're there to observe and report.  The analysis happens on this end."

He folds his hands on the table.

"Your job is to be a reliable pair of eyes inside that building."

<<if not hasVisited("INTRO-340 Why me")>>\
He pauses.  "You haven't asked why you."

He doesn't wait for you to answer.

"The assignment requires a credibly attractive woman under thirty who has completed <<term "Branch">> training and can hold a cover.  The talent pool matching those criteria is small.  I want you to have heard that out loud before you walk into that building."

He looks at his coffee instead of at you.

