:: INTRO-500 Question NYSE [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"Can you tell me more about the <<term "NYSE">> indicators?"

Robert takes a slow breath — the particular care he takes when Branch language has to carry weight it wasn't designed for.

"The pattern is escalation.  Members attending for six months or more show measurable personality shifts.  Progressive disinhibition.  Altered risk assessment.  And in several cases, desires that the subjects themselves describe as foreign.  'Not like me.'  That's a direct quote from an asset's notes."

He turns his coffee mug.

"And dreams.  Vivid, persistent, thematically consistent.  Several subjects reported dreaming about the club on nights they didn't attend."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-510 Question club [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"What do you know about the club itself?"

Robert nods — the question he expected first.

"Sizzle has been operating for approximately four years.  Heritage property, Victorian-era, corner lot.  Members-only, vetted entry.  Events several nights a week.  The membership is cross-sectional — professionals, creatives, some local names you'd recognize."

"The owner operates under the name Viktor Reeves.  Thin file — business registration, property records.  Nothing that triggers on its own.  The club runs clean on paper."

"Which is either good management or a very effective front.  That's what you're going to find out."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-520 Question risk [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"What's the risk assessment?"

"Moderate to high," Robert says, without the usual bureaucratic hedging.  "The <<term "NYSE">> element makes it unpredictable.  Prolonged exposure represents a genuine cognitive risk.  You will be affected.  The question is degree."

He lets that sit.

"Composure training gives you tools.  It gives you awareness.  But there's a difference between understanding <<term "NYSE">> indicators in a briefing room and experiencing them in the field."  He pauses.  "In a club."

"The physical risk is lower.  The danger here is cognitive, not physical.  Which, in my experience, is harder to see coming."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-530 Question previous [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
"Have you sent anyone in before?"

The pause is longer than usual.  Long enough that the waitress refills both your coffees and leaves before Robert speaks.

"No," he says.  "This is the Branch's first direct intelligence operation targeting Sizzle."

You wait.

"We considered it eighteen months ago.  The operational profile at the time didn't justify the risk.  It does now."

<<set _checkSkill to (typeof $player.currentComposure === "number") ? $player.currentComposure : $player.skills.composure.level>>
<<skillCheck "Composure" "2d6" _checkSkill 9>>
<<success>>
He's telling the truth, but it's not the whole truth.  He's deciding whether to tell you the rest now or later.  He decides on later.

"You'll be the first.  No playbook."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<<failure>>
You hear the answer and the careful pause after it.  If there is more behind the words, Robert keeps it locked down.

"You'll be the first.  No playbook."

[[Continue|INTRO-410 Rules]]
<</skillCheck>>
<</page>>


:: INTRO-600 Subtext [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert folds the paper and slides it across the table to you.  "Wednesday, 10 AM, the office.  Full ops briefing, documents, keys."

He picks up his coffee and finishes it in one long pull.

And then there's a moment.

Just a small hitch in Robert's efficiency.  He puts the mug down and his hand stays on it for a beat too long, and he looks at you, and his expression is exactly the same as it always is, except —

[[Continue|INTRO-610 Reading Robert]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-610 Reading Robert [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
/* Skill check: can the player read Robert's unease? */
<<set _checkSkill to (typeof $player.currentComposure === "number") ? $player.currentComposure : $player.skills.composure.level>>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
<<skillCheck "Composure" "2d6" _checkSkill 5>>
<<success>>
<<set $briefing.readRobert to true>>\
Except it isn't.

You've sat across from this man in dozens of briefings.  You've learned his rhythms — the pauses, the mug rotations, the way he uses silence.  You know his resting face.

And right now, under the steady professional surface, Robert Flett is worried.  Not about the operation.  He's worried about //you//.

[["You're worried about me."|INTRO-620 Called out]]
[[Say nothing.  Let it pass.|INTRO-700 Outside]]
<<failure>>
Except — you're not sure.  There's something there, in the way he's holding the mug, but you can't quite read it.  Two years of training and you still can't always crack Robert Flett.

Whatever it was, it passes.  He releases the mug and straightens in the booth.

[[Continue|INTRO-700 Outside]]
<</skillCheck>>
<</page>>


:: INTRO-620 Called out [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<<set $briefing.calledOut to true>>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
His eyes meet yours.  For a second — less than a second — the handler isn't there.  Just Robert, a man in his late forties who has been doing this work since before you were in high school, looking at someone he trained.

"I selected you for this assignment because you're the most qualified candidate available," he says.  And it's true.

"But yes."

Two words.  He doesn't elaborate.  He doesn't need to.

<<addNotification "You saw through Robert's composure.  He trusts you enough to let you.">>

[[Continue|INTRO-630 Moment passes]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-630 Moment passes [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Diner, Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
The waitress comes by and asks if they want anything else.  Robert says no thank you and reaches for his wallet.

The moment is over.  It existed for exactly as long as it needed to.

[[Continue|INTRO-700 Outside]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-700 Outside [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert pays for both coffees — he always does, out of pocket, never expensed.  You noticed that about six months in and never mentioned it.

Outside, <<term "Bank Street">> is doing what it does on a Monday morning.  Civil servants walking south toward the office towers with travel mugs and lanyards tucked inside their jackets.  A woman locking her bicycle to a rack outside a café that hasn't opened yet.

September sun on limestone.  Ottawa being unremarkably, specifically itself.

[[Continue|INTRO-710 Last words]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-710 Last words [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
Robert stands on the sidewalk, hands in his jacket pockets.  He glances east, then west.  Old habit.

"Wednesday," he says.  "Ten o'clock.  Bring ID photos — two passport-style, one casual."

<<if $briefing.readRobert>>He pauses.  Looks at you one more time with an expression that's almost the one from the diner.  Then he straightens his shoulders and puts the handler back on.

<</if>>"And <<playerRealName>>?"

You wait.

"Get some sleep this week.  You're going to want it."

[[Continue|INTRO-720 Departure]]
<</page>>


:: INTRO-720 Departure [daytime]
<<silently>>
<<set $header.location to "Bank Street, Ottawa">>
<<set $header.time to "Monday morning">>
<</silently>>\
<<header>>\
<<page>>\
He turns south, toward the office.  You watch him go — a man in an unremarkable jacket disappearing into the perfectly ordinary Monday morning.

<<if $briefing.calledOut>>He's worried about you.  You're a little worried about you too.  But not enough to walk away — not after two years of getting ready for exactly this.
<<elseif $briefing.readRobert>>He's worried about you.  You wish you could tell him not to be.  But that would require a certainty you don't have.
<<else>>A new city, a new apartment, a new name.  A club on Queen West where something is happening that the Branch can't explain.  And you, walking into it with two years of training and a composure that hasn't been tested yet.
<</if>>

Wednesday.  Ten o'clock.  ID photos.

[[Your assignment begins.|INTRO-800 End]]
<</page>>


